annotateInitialSeed

annotateInitialSeed.Rd
annotateInitialSeed(
  ms1_file = "data.csv",
  ms2_file = NULL,
  metdna_version = c("version2", "version1"),
  ms2_type = c("mgf", "mzXML", "msp", "cef"),
  path = ".",
  polarity = c("positive", "negative"),
  instrument = c("SciexTripleTOF", "AgilentQTOF", "BrukerQTOF", "ThermoOrbitrap",
    "ThermoExploris", "AgilentDTIMMS", "BrukerTIMS"),
  lib = c("zhuMetLib", "zhuMetLib_orbitrap", "fiehnHilicLib"),
  column = c("hilic", "rp"),
  ce = c("30", "10", "20", "35,15", "40", "50", "NCE10", "NCE20", "NCE30", "NCE40",
    "NCE50", "SCE20_30_40%", "SNCE20_30_40%"),
  method_lc = c("Amide12min", "Amide23min", "Other"),
  excluded_adduct = NULL,
  is_rt_calibration = FALSE,
  mz_tol = 25,
  pf_rt_range = 0,
  tolerance_rt_range = 30,
  pf_ccs_range = 0,
  tolerance_ccs_range = 2,
  is_filter = TRUE,
  is_rt_score = TRUE,
  is_ccs_score = FALSE,
  is_ms2_score = TRUE,
  is_include_precursor = TRUE,
  int_ms2_min_abs = 50,
  int_ms2_min_relative = 0.01,
  mz_tol_combine_ms1_ms2 = 25,
  rt_tol_combine_ms1_ms2 = 10,
  ccs_tol_combine_ms1_ms2 = NULL,
  mz_tol_ms2 = 35,
  dp_cutoff = 0.8,
  matched_frag_cutoff = 1,
  direction = c("reverse", "forward"),
  scoring_approach = c("dp", "bonanza", "hybrid", "gnps"),
  test_adduct_version = c("version2", "version1"),
  is_plot_ms2 = TRUE
)

Arguments

ms1_file

The name of ms1 peak table. Column 1 is "name", Column 2 is "mz" and column is "rt".
ms2_file

Default: NULL
metdna_version

'version1', 'version2'. Default: "version1"
ms2_type

"mgf", "mzXML", "msp", "cef"
path

Default: '.'
instrument

The instrument you used to acquire data. "SciexTripleTOF", "AgilentQTOF", "BrukerQTOF", "ThermoOrbitrap", "ThermoExploris", "AgilentDTIMMS", "BrukerTIMS". Default: "SciexTripleTOF"
lib

Default: 'zhuMetLib'
column

"hilic", "rp"
ce

"10", "20", "30", "35,15", "40", "50". Default: "30"
method_lc

'Amide12min', 'Amide23min'. Default: 'Amide12min'
excluded_adduct

adduct list for exclusion. Default: NULL
is_rt_calibration

Default: FALSE
mz_tol

ms1 match. Default: 25 ppm
tolerance_rt_range

maxmium rt tolerance. Default: 30 s
tolerance_ccs_range

maxmium rt tolerance. Default: 2

is_filterWhether filter candidates whose rt/ccs exceed the maximum tolerance. Default: FALSE

is_rt_scorelogical vector. Default: TRUE

is_ccs_scorelogical vector. Default: FALSE

is_ms2_scorelogical vector. Default: TRUE

is_include_precursorDefault: TRUE

int_ms2_min_absDefault: 30

int_ms2_min_relativeDefault: 0.01

mz_tol_combine_ms1_ms2Default: 25 ppm

rt_tol_combine_ms1_ms2Default: 10 s

ccs_tol_combine_ms1_ms2Only appliable for IM-MS data. Default: NULL

mz_tol_ms2Default: 35 ppm

dp_cutoffThe cutoff of dot product. Default is 0.8.

matched_frag_cutoffThe cutoff of matched fragment number. Default: 1

directionReserve which direct dot product. 'reverse', 'forward'. Default: 'reverse'

scoring_approachspectral match approach, including 'dp', 'bonanza', 'hybrid', 'gnps'. Default: 'dp'.

is_plot_ms2Output MS2 match plot or not. Default: TRUE

pf_rt_tolpenalty-free rt range. Default: 0 s

pf_ccs_tolpenalty-free rt range. Default: 0 Return the annotation result. Annotate peak using MS/MS spectra in in-house database. Zhiwei Zhou, Xiaotao Shen, Yandong Yin
